# Club Website Design Rules

**Core principle:** Every spacing value, color, radius, weight, and animation must reference the project design system. Inconsistency signals vibe-coding.

- **Colors:** No default purple gradients unless brand. No sparkles/emojis in hero headings. No generic glowing hovers.
- **Typography:** Consistent weight hierarchy, uniform line-height and paragraph spacing. Use the defined type scale only.
- **Layout:** Same component placement across pages. 2–3 border-radius values max. Hover lift 2–4px max. Icons sized to text. No non-functional social icons.
- **Motion:** Use cubic-bezier easing; stagger intentionally; every animation has a purpose.
- **UX:** Loading states for async actions; progress on buttons; working toggles/carousels; skeleton screens for data-heavy sections.
- **Copy:** No em-dash overuse. No vague phrases ("Launch faster", "Build your dreams"). No fake testimonials or placeholder names (e.g. "Sarah Chen").

Before adding new UI: check `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` for tokens and patterns.
